trans-unit.source: Module Overview
trans-unit.target: Module Overview

trans-unit.source: You can use the <ui>Execute Python Script</ui> module to run Python code from experiments in Azure Machine Learning.
trans-unit.target: You can use the <ui>Execute Python Script</ui> module to run Python code from experiments in Azure Machine Learning.

trans-unit.source: By integrating your IPython notebooks with Azure Machine Learning, you can perform custom tasks, create visualizations, and share your models with the world.
trans-unit.target: By integrating your IPython notebooks with Azure Machine Learning, you can perform custom tasks, create visualizations, and share your models with the world.

trans-unit.source: How to Use Execute Python Script
trans-unit.target: How to Use Execute Python Script

trans-unit.source: To configure the <ui>Execute Python Script</ui> module, you provide a set of inputs, and type the Python code to execute in the <ui>Python script</ui> text box.
trans-unit.target: To configure the <ui>Execute Python Script</ui> module, you provide a set of inputs, and type the Python code to execute in the <ui>Python script</ui> text box.

trans-unit.source: <embeddedLabel>Inputs</embeddedLabel>.
trans-unit.target: <embeddedLabel>Inputs</embeddedLabel>.

trans-unit.source: The module has these inputs:
trans-unit.target: The module has these inputs:

trans-unit.source: <ui>Dataset1</ui>.
trans-unit.target: <ui>Dataset1</ui>.

trans-unit.source: An optional dataset from your <token>ProductName</token> workspace, containing input data or values.
trans-unit.target: An optional dataset from your <token>ProductName</token> workspace, containing input data or values.

trans-unit.source: <ui>Dataset2</ui>.
trans-unit.target: <ui>Dataset2</ui>.

trans-unit.source: A second dataset, also optional.
trans-unit.target: A second dataset, also optional.

trans-unit.source: <ui>Script bundle</ui>.
trans-unit.target: <ui>Script bundle</ui>.

trans-unit.source: A zipped file containing custom resources
trans-unit.target: A zipped file containing custom resources

trans-unit.source: Any file that is placed in your ZIP file will be available for use during execution time.
trans-unit.target: Any file that is placed in your ZIP file will be available for use during execution time.

trans-unit.source: If there is a directory structure present it will be preserved, with the only change being that you must prepend a directory called ‘src’ to the path.
trans-unit.target: If there is a directory structure present it will be preserved, with the only change being that you must prepend a directory called ‘src’ to the path.

trans-unit.source: Before you can connect the Script Bundle to the <ui>Execute Python Script</ui> module, the ZIP file must be already present in the Studio workspace.
trans-unit.target: Before you can connect the Script Bundle to the <ui>Execute Python Script</ui> module, the ZIP file must be already present in the Studio workspace.

trans-unit.source: To upload a ZIP file to your workspace, click <ui>New</ui>, click <ui>Dataset</ui>, and then select <ui>From local file</ui> and the <ui>Zip file</ui> option.
trans-unit.target: To upload a ZIP file to your workspace, click <ui>New</ui>, click <ui>Dataset</ui>, and then select <ui>From local file</ui> and the <ui>Zip file</ui> option.

trans-unit.target: <embeddedLabel>Outputs</embeddedLabel>.

trans-unit.target: The module returns these outputs:

trans-unit.target: <ui>Results Dataset</ui>.

trans-unit.source: A dataset with the results of any computations performed by the embedded Python code.
trans-unit.target: A dataset with the results of any computations performed by the embedded Python code.

trans-unit.source: The dataset uses the internal dataset format.
trans-unit.target: The dataset uses the internal dataset format.
